{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesS3\/documentation\/EnsemblesS3"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"EnsemblesS3 provides "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesS3\/documentation\/EnsemblesS3\/S3CloudFileSystem"},{"type":"text","text":", an implementation of the Ensembles "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CloudFileSystem"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol that stores sync data in an Amazon S3 bucket. It uses the official "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/awslabs\/aws-sdk-swift"},{"type":"text","text":" for all API operations."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"S3 is a natural fit for Ensembles — it’s highly durable, globally available, and cost-effective for the small files that Ensembles exchanges. S3-compatible services (MinIO, DigitalOcean Spaces, Backblaze B2, Cloudflare R2) can also be used by configuring the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"S3Client"},{"type":"text","text":" with a custom endpoint."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"anchor":"S3-as-a-File-System","type":"heading","text":"S3 as a File System"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"S3 is a flat key-value store, not a hierarchical file system. "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesS3\/documentation\/EnsemblesS3\/S3CloudFileSystem"},{"type":"text","text":" simulates directory semantics using key prefixes and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/"},{"text":" delimiters — the standard S3 convention. For example, the Ensembles path ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ensembleId\/events\/data.json"},{"text":" maps to the S3 key ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"prefix\/ensembleId\/events\/data.json"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Directory creation writes a zero-byte marker object with a trailing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/"},{"text":" in the key. Directory listing uses ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ListObjectsV2"},{"text":" with a delimiter to discover “subdirectories” via common prefixes.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Authentication","type":"heading","anchor":"Authentication"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The AWS SDK for Swift supports multiple credential sources (environment variables, IAM roles, SSO, credential files). Your app creates and configures an "},{"code":"S3Client","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", then injects it:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import EnsemblesS3","import AWSS3","","let s3Client = try await S3Client()  \/\/ Uses default credential chain","let cloudFileSystem = S3CloudFileSystem(","    client: s3Client,","    bucketName: \"my-ensembles-bucket\",","    keyPrefix: \"sync\/\"  \/\/ Optional: isolate Ensembles data under a prefix",")"]},{"level":3,"text":"Setup","type":"heading","anchor":"Setup"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let ensemble = CoreDataEnsemble(","    ensembleIdentifier: \"MainStore\",","    persistentStoreURL: storeURL,","    managedObjectModelURL: modelURL,","    cloudFileSystem: S3CloudFileSystem(","        client: s3Client,","        bucketName: \"my-bucket\",","        keyPrefix: \"ensembles\/\"","    )",")","try await ensemble?.attachPersistentStore()"]},{"level":3,"text":"Key Prefix","type":"heading","anchor":"Key-Prefix"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesS3\/documentation\/EnsemblesS3\/S3CloudFileSystem\/keyPrefix"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter isolates Ensembles data within a shared bucket. For example, with "},{"code":"keyPrefix: \"ensembles\/\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", the path "},{"code":"\/MyStore\/events\/abc.json","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" maps to the S3 key "},{"code":"ensembles\/MyStore\/events\/abc.json","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". A trailing "},{"code":"\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is added automatically if omitted."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"keyPrefix"},{"type":"text","text":" is empty (the default), Ensembles data is stored at the bucket root."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"anchor":"S3-Compatible-Services","type":"heading","text":"S3-Compatible Services"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To use an S3-compatible service, configure the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"S3Client"},{"type":"text","text":" with a custom endpoint:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let config = try await S3Client.S3ClientConfiguration()","config.endpoint = \"https:\/\/s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com\"  \/\/ or MinIO, R2, etc.","let s3Client = S3Client(config: config)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Error-Handling","type":"heading","text":"Error Handling"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"AWS SDK errors are mapped to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EnsembleError"},{"type":"text","text":" cases:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AccessDenied"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"InvalidAccessKeyId"},{"text":", and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SignatureDoesNotMatch"},{"text":" map to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EnsembleError\/authenticationFailure"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NoSuchKey"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NoSuchBucket"},{"text":", and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NotFound"},{"text":" map to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EnsembleError\/fileAccessFailed"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"All other errors map to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EnsembleError\/serverError"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Dependencies","type":"heading","text":"Dependencies"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This module depends on the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"AWS SDK for Swift","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"AWS SDK for Swift"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/awslabs\/aws-sdk-swift"},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AWSS3"},{"type":"text","text":" module)."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An Amazon S3-based cloud backend for Ensembles."}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"EnsemblesS3"}],"role":"collection","externalID":"EnsemblesS3","roleHeading":"Framework","symbolKind":"module","title":"EnsemblesS3"},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Cloud-File-System","title":"Cloud File System","identifiers":["doc:\/\/EnsemblesS3\/documentation\/EnsemblesS3\/S3CloudFileSystem"]}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/ensembless3"]}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"references":{"doc://EnsemblesS3/documentation/EnsemblesS3/S3CloudFileSystem":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"S3CloudFileSystem","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesS3\/documentation\/EnsemblesS3\/S3CloudFileSystem","url":"\/documentation\/ensembless3\/s3cloudfilesystem","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A cloud file system backed by Amazon S3, using the AWS SDK for Swift."}],"title":"S3CloudFileSystem","role":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"S3CloudFileSystem"}]},"doc://EnsemblesS3/documentation/EnsemblesS3/S3CloudFileSystem/keyPrefix":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesS3\/documentation\/EnsemblesS3\/S3CloudFileSystem\/keyPrefix","title":"keyPrefix","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Optional key prefix within the bucket (e.g. “ensembles\/”)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"If set, all keys are prefixed with this value.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/ensembless3\/s3cloudfilesystem\/keyprefix","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"let"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"keyPrefix"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"}]},"https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-swift":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"AWS SDK for Swift"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/awslabs\/aws-sdk-swift","title":"AWS SDK for Swift","type":"link","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/awslabs\/aws-sdk-swift"},"doc://EnsemblesS3/documentation/EnsemblesS3":{"role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/ensembless3","identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesS3\/documentation\/EnsemblesS3","title":"EnsemblesS3","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An Amazon S3-based cloud backend for Ensembles."}]}}}